byline.contributor: Anemona Hartocollis reported from New York and Yamiche Alcindor from Washington. Reporting was contributed from Julie Turkewitz in Denver, Jess Bidgood in Boston, Alan Blinder in Atlanta, Fernanda Santos in Phoenix, Nick Corasaniti and Katie Rogers in Washington, Christina Capecchi in St. Paul, Mitch Smith in Chicago, and Emma G. Fitzsimmons and Giovanni Russonello in New York.
byline.original: By ANEMONA HARTOCOLLIS and YAMICHE ALCINDOR

lead_paragraph: Hundreds of thousands of women gathered in Washington and other cities across the country Saturday in a kind of counterinauguration after President Trump took office on Friday.

headline.main: Women’s March Highlights as Huge Crowds Protest Trump: ‘We’re Not Going Away’
